{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<P>This protein, LolB, is known so far only in the gamma subdivision of the Proteobacteria. It is a processed, lipid-modified outer membrane protein. In Escherichia coli, lipoproteins are anchored to the periplasmic side of either the inner or outer membrane through N-terminal lipids, depending on the lipoprotein-sorting signal present at position 2 [[cite:PUB00007680]]. Five Lol proteins are involved in the sorting and outer membrane localization of lipoproteins. LolCDE, an ATP binding cassette (ABC) transporter, in the inner membrane releases outer membrane-directed lipoproteins from the inner membrane in an ATP-dependent manner, leading to the formation of a water-soluble complex between the lipoprotein and LolA. The LolA-lipoprotein complex crosses the periplasm and then interacts with outer membrane receptor LolB, which is essential for the anchoring of lipoproteins to the outer membrane.</P>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1iwm", "name" "Crystal Structure of the Outer Membrane Lipoprotein Receptor, LolB"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029046", "name" "Lipoprotein localisation LolA/LolB/LppX", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"cdd" {"cd16326" "LolB, an outer membrane lipoprotein receptor"}, "hamap" {"MF_00233" "Outer-membrane lipoprotein LolB [lolB]"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00548" "lipoprotein insertase outer membrane protein LolB"}, "pfam" {"PF03550" "Outer membrane lipoprotein LolB"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Outer membrane lipoprotein LolB", "short" "OM_lipoprot_LolB"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 14, "proteomes" 1703, "taxa" 7972, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 9086, "sets" 0, "proteins" 9085, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 7001}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Pro